          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was carried out at the Los",
                "Alamos Neutron Science Center-Weapons Neutron Research."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "For target a polyamide backing of 35 mu-g/cm2 areal",
                "density was coated with a 50 mu-g/cm2 layer of gold",
                "for electrical conductivity. 238UF4 was deposited on",
                "top of the gold, and the deposit has an areal",
                "thickness of 132 mu-g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin Frisch-gridded ionization chamber was",
                "chosen for fission detection, mainly due to its high",
                "efficiency, good energy resolution (0.5 - 1.0%) and",
                "nearly 4PI solid angle coverage. The ionization",
                "chamber was operated with P10 fill gas (90% argon and",
                "10% methane) at 1.25 kPa."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The timing structure of proton and neutron",
                "pulses is a 625 mu-s long macropulse consisting of",
                "micropulses with 1.8 mu-s separation and widths of",
                "about 250 ps. The macropulse repetition rate was 40 Hz.",
                "The available neutron energy range is typically",
                "hundreds of keV to hundreds of MeV. The flight-path",
                "length was determined to be L = 9.596 +- 0.015 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A beam of 800-MeV protons from the LANSCE",
                "accelerator impinges on a tungsten target at WNR and",
                "creates high-energy neutrons through spallation."
              ]
            }
          ],
